# ---- Deploying on Vercel (recommended for live) ----
# Set this in the Vercel project (Settings → Environment Variables), NOT here in
# the client bundle. The serverless proxy at api/[...path].js injects it as a
# Bearer token, so the key stays server-side and one key serves every viewer.
# OPENF1_API_KEY=your-key-here
#
# In production the app calls the proxy same-origin at /api/v1 automatically —
# no client config needed. Optional knobs for the proxy: CACHE_TTL_MS, UPSTREAM_GAP_MS.

# ---- Local dev ----
# Vite only exposes vars prefixed with VITE_. Copy this file to .env.local.
# By default local dev hits OpenF1 directly (free historical data, no key).
# Point the app elsewhere (e.g. the standalone proxy) only if you need to:
# VITE_OPENF1_BASE_URL=http://localhost:8787/v1

# ---- server/proxy.mjs (standalone Node proxy: npm run proxy) ----
# Same role as the Vercel function, for non-Vercel hosting. Never commit a real key.
# OPENF1_API_KEY=your-key-here
# PORT=8787
# CACHE_TTL_MS=2000
